  "local_port": 47314,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "If you block someone on Instagram could they still see you in the followers list of an account that didn't block them and they already know?",
  "response": "When you block someone on Instagram, they will no longer be able to see your profile, posts, or stories. They also won't be able to find your profile in search or see when you're online. However, blocking someone on Instagram does not affect their ability to see your interactions with other accounts that they follow and that haven't blocked them.\n\nIf you appear in the followers list of a mutual account (an account that both you and the blocked person follow and which hasn't blocked either of you), the person you blocked can still see your username in that followers list. They will see your username as it appears on that account's followers list, but they won't be able to access your profile from there.\n\nRemember, the extent to which someone can see your activity on Instagram after you've blocked them can depend on your privacy settings and the settings of the account where your username appears. If the account where your username appears is public, then anyone, including someone you've blocked, can see the followers list. If the account is private, only approved followers can see the followers list, so the person you blocked would need to be following that account to see your username there.\n\nIt's also worth noting that Instagram's policies and features can change, so it's a good idea to stay updated with the latest information directly from Instagram's help center or support resources.",
